CIC/References/Context_Objects.html.body:
Context information
Context information indicates various states of a client. To provide context, include context objects when sending event messages with the CIC APIs. Context information must reflect states at the time when user has spoken. The following are the available context objects.

AudioPlayer.PlaybackState
Device.DeviceState
Clova.FreetalkState
Clova.Location
Clova.SavedPlace
Speaker.VolumeState

AudioPlayer.PlaybackState 
PlaybackState is a message format that contains information of media currently playing or previously played. This information can be sent to an extension that provides a music streaming service.
Message format
{
  "header": {
    "namespace": "AudioPlayer",
    "name": "PlaybackState"
  },
  "payload": {
    "offsetInMilliseconds": {{number}},
    "totalInMilliseconds": {{number}},
    "playerActivity": {{string}},
    "stream": {{AudioStreamObject}}
  }
}

Payload field



Field name
Type
Field description
Required




offsetInMilliseconds
number
Recently played media's last playback point (offset). Unit is millisecond. You can leave the field empty when playerActivity is "IDLE".
No


playerActivity
string
Indicates a player state. Available values are:"IDLE": In an idle state"PLAYING": In a playing state"PAUSED": In a paused state"STOPPED": In a stopped state
Yes


stream
AudioStreamObject
An object that contains details of media currently playing. You can leave the field empty when playerActivity is "IDLE". Enter media details (stream object) returned from AudioPlayer.Play or AudioPlayer.StreamDelivered directive message.
No


totalInMilliseconds
number
Total length of the media recently played. Unit is millisecond. You can leave the field empty when playerActivity is "IDLE".
No



Message example
Example 1: When playback has stopped
// Case 1: When playback has stopped
{
  "header": {
    "namespace": "AudioPlayer",
    "name": "PlaybackState"
  },
  "payload": {
    "offsetInMilliseconds": 1,
    "totalInMilliseconds": 100,
    "playerActivity": "STOPPED",
    "stream": {
      "beginAtInMilliseconds": 0,
      "progressReport": {
        "progressReportDelayInMilliseconds": null,
        "progressReportIntervalInMilliseconds": null,
        "progressReportPositionInMilliseconds": 60000
      },
      "token": "TR-NM-17740107",
      "url": "clova:TR-NM-17740107"
    }
  }
}

Example 2: When a player is inactivated
{
  "header": {
    "namespace": "AudioPlayer",
    "name": "PlaybackState"
  },
  "payload": {
    "playerActivity": "IDLE"
  }
}

See also

AudioPlayer.Play
AudioPlayer.StreamDeliver
AudioPlayer.StreamRequested

Device.DeviceState 
DeviceState is a message format that sends device state information, such as a current local time in a user's device.
Message format
{
  "header": {
    "namespace": "Device",
    "name": "DeviceState"
  },
  "payload": {
    "localTime": {{string}}
  }
}

Payload field



Field name
Type
Field description
Required




localTime
string
Current time set in a client device (ISO 8601 format)
Yes



Message example
{
  "header": {
    "namespace": "Device",
    "name": "DeviceState"
  },
  "payload": {
    "localTime": "2017-04-06T13:34:15.074361+08:28"
  }
}

See also

SpeechRecognizer.Recognize

Clova.FreetalkState 
FreetalkState is a message format that shows a state of the Clova Freetalk service at a client side.
Message format
{
  "header": {
      "namespace": "Clova",
      "name": "FreetalkState"
  },
  "payload": {
      "foreground": {{boolean}},
      "reprompt": {{boolean}}
  }
}

Payload field



Field name
Type
Field description
Required




foreground
boolean
Whether the Freetalk mode is activated or not true: Activated.false: Inactivated.
Yes


reprompt
boolean
Whether reprompted for a user response or not. This state value verifies whether a user was reprompted for a response or not when the user did not give input for a specified time. true: Reprompted for a user response and the Freetalk mode will be finished.false: Did not reprompted for a user response and is waiting for a response.
Yes



Remarks
The Freetalk mode is available only in English at the moment. If the foreground field is set to true, set the lang field of a Recognize event message of SpeechRecognizer API to "en".
Message example
{
  "header": {
      "namespace": "Clova",
      "name": "FreetalkState"
  },
  "payload": {
      "foreground": flase,
      "reprompt": true
  }
}

See also

SpeechRecognizer.Recognize

Clova.Location 
Message format that sends client's current location information. You can obtain location information from GPS, base stations or network devices and send it to CIC.
Message format
{
  "header": {
    "namespace": "Clova",
    "name": "Location"
  },
  "payload": {
    "latitude": {{string}},
    "longitude": {{string}},
    "refreshedAt": {{string}}
  }
}

Payload field



Field name
Type
Field description
Required




latitude
string
Latitude
Yes


longitude
string
Longitude
Yes


refreshedAt
string
The time when the location was last checked (UTC, ISO 8601 format)
Yes



Message example
{
  "header": {
    "namespace": "Clova",
    "name": "Location"
  },
  "payload": {
    "latitude": "37.3594915",
    "longitude": "127.1032242",
    "refreshedAt": "2017-04-06T13:34:15.074361+08:28"
  }
}

See also

SpeechRecognizer.Recognize

Clova.SavedPlace 
Message format that sends client's pre-saved location information.
Message format
{
  "header": {
    "namespace": "Clova",
    "name": "SavedPlace"
  },
  "payload": {
    "places": [
      {
        "latitude": {{string}},
        "longitude": {{string}},
        "refreshedAt": {{string}}
        "name": {{string}}
      }
    ]
  }
}

Payload field



Field name
Type
Field description
Required




places[]
object array
An object array that contains pre-saved location information
Yes


places[].latitude
string
Latitude
Yes


places[].longitude
string
Longitude
Yes


places[].name
string
The name of the location saved. Available values are: 회사집
Yes


places[].refreshedAt
string
The time when the location was saved (UTC, ISO 8601 format)
Yes



Message example
{
  "header": {
    "namespace": "Clova",
    "name": "SavedPlace"
  },
  "payload": {
    "places": [
      {
        "latitude": "37.3594915",
        "longitude": "127.1032242",
        "refreshedAt": "2017-04-06T13:34:15.074361+08:28"
        "name": "집"
      },
      {
        "latitude": "36.3542315",
        "longitude": "125.1345242",
        "refreshedAt": "2017-03-12T10:21:33.089723+08:28"
        "name": "회사"
      }
    ]
  }
}

See also

SpeechRecognizer.Recognize

Speaker.VolumeState 
Message format that contains speaker information at the time when a user has spoken, such as volume size or whether speaker is muted or unmuted.
Message format
{
  "header": {
      "namespace": "Speaker",
      "name": "VolumeState"
  },
  "payload": {
      "volume": {{number}},
      "muted": {{boolean}}
  }
}

Payload field



Field name
Type
Field description
Required




muted
boolean
Whether muted or unmuted
Yes


volume
number
Speaker's current volume size (0-10)
Yes



Message example
{
  "header": {
      "namespace": "Speaker",
      "name": "VolumeState"
  },
  "payload": {
      "volume": 8,
      "muted": false
  }
}

See also

SpeechRecognizer.Recognize

CIC/References/ContentTemplates/CardList.body:
CardList Template
Displays information in a card list format. CardList has several card types. For each card type, the card object has different field configuration.



Card type
Type description
card object fields




Type1
Displays content's image, title, and description.
description, imageUrl, referenceText, referenceUrl, title


Type2
Displays content's image, title, description, and link.
description, imageUrl, linkUrl, referenceText, referenceUrl, title


Type3
Displays video content.
description, imageUrl, referenceText, referenceUrl, title, videoUrl


Type4
Displays news content.
description, press, pressIconUrl, publishDate, title




Note!
See Screen UI example for available display formats for each card type.


Template field



Field name
Type
Field description
Required




cardList[]
object array
An object array that displays a list of cards
Yes


cardList[].description
StringObject array
An object array that contains a content description
No


cardList[].imageUrl
URLObject
An object that contains an image URL
No


cardList[].linkUrl
URLObject
An object that contains a content URL
No


cardList[].press
StringObject
An object that contains a press name
No


cardList[].pressIconUrl
URLObject
An object that contains a press icon URL
No


cardList[].publishDate
DateObject
An object that contains an article publishing date
No


cardList[].referenceText
StringObject
An object that contains text information of a source
No


cardList[].referenceURL
URLObject
An object that contains a source URL
No


cardList[].title
StringObject
An object that contains a content title
No


cardList[].videoUrl
URLObject
An object that contains a video URL
No


subType
string
Card type delimiter. You can specify one of the four types. Type1Type2Type3Type4Note!Type1, Type2, Type3 are displayed as an empty string at the moment. You must determine the type from field configuration of the card object.
Yes


type
string
Content template delimiter. The value is always "CardList".
Yes



Template Example
// Type1, Type2 example:
// User request: 공포 영화 추천해줘 (Request to recommend horror movies)

{
