CIC/References/ContentTemplates/Text.htm.body:
Text Template
Provides text data to display. It is used to display text with highlights, paragraph text or table text.

Note!
See Screen UI example for available display formats of the Text template.


Template field



Field name
Type
Field description
Required




bgUrl
URLObject
An object that contains a URL to an image to be displayed in background
No


highlightText
StringObject or NumberObject
An object that contains highlighted text or number with digit grouping symbols.
No


imageUrl
URLObject
An object that contains an image URL
No


linkUrl
URLObject
An object that contains a URL which directs users to a web map when a map image is included
No


mainText
StringObject
An object that contains main text
No


paragraphText
StringObject
An object that contains paragraph text
No


referenceText
StringObject
An object that contains text information of a source
No


referenceURL
URLObject
An object that contains a source URL
No


sentenceText
StringObject
An object that contains sentence text
No


subText
StringObject
An object that contain sub text
No


tableList[]
object array
An object array that contains table text. The table has two columns.
No


tableList[].item1
StringObject
An object that contains text to be displayed in the first column
No


tableList[].item2
StringObject
An object that contains text to be displayed in the second column
No


tableList[].item2Link
URLObject or PhoneNumberObject
An object that contains link URL or phone number of the text in the second column
No


type
string
Content template delimiter. The value is always "ImageText".
Yes



